data.title: About - The Official CROWN Act
data.description: The CROWN Act stands for "Create a Respectful and Open World for Natural Hair," created in 2019 to ensure protection against discrimination based on race-based hairstyles by extending statutory protection to hair texture and protective styles such as braids, locs, twists, and knots in the workplace and public schools.
